primaryTopic.definition: The Department of Planning, Industry and Environment brings together specialists in urban and regional planning, natural resources, industry, environment, heritage, Aboriginal and social housing, and regional New South Wales. The department brings together the functions from the former Planning and Environment and Industry clusters.
